    "industrial_process_notes": "The monomer was first synthesized in 1956 (Sprecht); a 1957 patent covered its use as a rodent repellent. The polymer's distinctive thermoresponsive behavior in aqueous solution was first reported in 1968, and research interest expanded significantly in the 1980s once its applications were recognized. Made via free-radical polymerization (homo-, co-, or terpolymerization for property tuning).",
